{\an1}Yeah. Colin's
taking me to Eclipse.

15:33.098 --> 15:35.017
Ooh!<i> Tres chic.</i>

15:35.100 --> 15:36.393
Yeah. Give those
to the others, would ya?

15:36.477 --> 15:38.729
Okay. See you.
Bye. Love you. Bye!

15:38.812 --> 15:40.981
{\an1}Bye!

15:41.065 --> 15:43.025
{\an1}(laughs)

15:43.108 --> 15:45.152
Well, that was strange.

15:45.235 --> 15:46.820
Well, rumor has it
the Three Wise Men

15:46.904 --> 15:49.239
{\an3}didn't show up in
Bethlehem till January.

15:50.074 --> 15:52.868
{\an3}Oh, man!
Internet In a Box!

15:52.951 --> 15:54.203
{\an3}I've been saving
up for this.

15:54.286 --> 15:56.163
Whoa. Whoa. Check it out.

15:56.246 --> 15:58.749
How classy.
For the driving enthusiast.

15:58.832 --> 16:00.834
Likewise. Even matches my car.

16:00.918 --> 16:02.336
What did you get, Val?

16:02.419 --> 16:04.004
{\an1}"Mirror, mirror,
on the wall."

16:04.088 --> 16:07.549
Aren't any of you the least bit
disturbed by any of this?

16:07.633 --> 16:09.176
{\an3}I mean, didn't you get
a good look at them?

16:09.259 --> 16:10.177
Kelly and Colin?

16:10.260 --> 16:11.512
{\an1}No. The ghosts
from Christmas Past.

16:11.595 --> 16:12.930
Yes, Colin and Kelly.

16:13.013 --> 16:14.223
I mean, you don't think
this is manic behavior?

16:14.306 --> 16:15.224
{\an3}You heard
what she said.

16:15.307 --> 16:16.725
{\an3}Her father gave her
some extra cash to blow.

16:16.809 --> 16:17.851
She's having
a good time.

16:17.935 --> 16:19.019
What's the big deal?

16:19.103 --> 16:20.062
{\an1}I don't know
about you people,

16:20.145 --> 16:22.272
but I feel loved.

16:22.356 --> 16:23.232
(laughter all around)

16:23.315 --> 16:25.943
Well, they were blowing
much more than cash.

16:26.026 --> 16:27.027
What? You think Colin
was high again?

16:27.111 --> 16:28.112
They both were.

16:28.195 --> 16:29.446
{\an1}STEVE:
Kelly high?

16:29.530 --> 16:31.323
No way. think so.

16:31.407 --> 16:33.117
She's been all over Colin
from the beginning about this.

16:33.200 --> 16:34.743
{\an3}That is kind
of a far stretch.

16:34.827 --> 16:35.744
I don't think she'd be using

16:35.828 --> 16:37.037
after what she went through
with her mother.

16:37.121 --> 16:38.414
{\an1}Yeah. And that
whole intervention

16:38.497 --> 16:39.915
thing with Dylan.

16:39.998 --> 16:41.417
Oh, guys, please. Come on!

16:41.500 --> 16:42.835
I mean, all I keep hearing about

16:42.918 --> 16:44.253
is Dylan
and Kelly's mother and David.

16:44.336 --> 16:45.462
I mean, when does

16:45.546 --> 16:47.131
{\an3}anybody learn anything
from the lessons

16:47.214 --> 16:48.799
{\an3}of the past?
I mean, trust me.

16:48.882 --> 16:50.134
These are guilt gifts.

16:50.217 --> 16:52.136
Kelly's getting high.

17:01.186 --> 17:03.939
{\an1}Hi. Don't you
love this place?

17:04.021 --> 17:06.066
{\an1}I brought my parents
here last week.

17:08.359 --> 17:10.779
For madame, the risotto
with black truffles.

17:10.863 --> 17:12.740
{\an1}Thank you.

17:12.823 --> 17:14.782
And, monsieur, our roasted rack
of lamb with Tuscan beans.

17:14.867 --> 17:16.410
Thanks.

17:17.994 --> 17:19.121
I only order this

17:19.204 --> 17:20.289
{\an3}'cause I like
the little booties.

17:20.372 --> 17:22.624
Will there be anything else?

17:22.708 --> 17:24.084
No, no. We're
fine. Thanks.

17:26.211 --> 17:29.298
I don't even know
how you can eat meat.

17:29.381 --> 17:31.133
{\an3}Easy. With a knife
and fork.

17:31.216 --> 17:32.301
Baah!

17:32.384 --> 17:34.136
Baah! Baah!

17:34.219 --> 17:36.847
{\an3}Stop it.

17:38.849 --> 17:40.058
Go ahead. Try your risotto.

17:40.142 --> 17:42.936
I'm not really that hungry.

17:43.020 --> 17:44.938
Yeah. Me neither.

17:45.022 --> 17:47.107
Okay. My turn.

17:47.191 --> 17:48.484
{\an3}Where's our
little power pack?

17:48.567 --> 17:50.319
It's gone.

17:50.402 --> 17:51.737
I did it.

17:51.820 --> 17:53.989
Gone? Come on.
You got to be kidding me.

17:54.072 --> 17:55.282
{\an3}Kelly, there
was enough

17:55.365 --> 17:56.992
left for both of us.

17:57.076 --> 17:59.495
Look, you've been going through
it twice as fast as I have.

17:59.578 --> 18:00.996
You're crazy.

18:01.079 --> 18:01.830
Why are you making
such a big deal out of it?

18:01.914 --> 18:03.499
Why don't we just
go get some more?

18:03.582 --> 18:04.666
We can't. Not from Paul.

18:04.750 --> 18:05.834
He's... he's all tapped out.

18:05.918 --> 18:08.504
{\an3}Come on.
Let's split.

18:08.587 --> 18:11.507
I don't want to sit here
jonesing all night.

18:11.590 --> 18:14.092
I'm certainly not going to eat.

18:19.723 --> 18:21.016
(knocking on door)

18:21.099 --> 18:22.684
It's not locked.

18:25.103 --> 18:26.230
Hey, Brandon.

18:26.313 --> 18:27.189
Hey, Joe.

18:27.272 --> 18:28.565
{\an3}You're on
campus late.

18:28.649 --> 18:30.359
Well, the news never sleeps.

18:30.442 --> 18:32.069
{\an6}Besides, I was
kind of hoping
I'd find you here.

18:32.152 --> 18:33.987
Oh, yeah? What's going on?

18:34.071 --> 18:36.657
{\an5}Well, we got this
press release at
the paper today.

18:36.740 --> 18:39.159
{\an5}I just kind of
wanted to follow up
with you on it.

18:39.243 --> 18:40.994
{\an1}What press release
is that?

18:41.078 --> 18:42.663
{\an3}You're quoted.
You should know.

18:42.746 --> 18:45.082
Right. The ankle thing.

18:45.165 --> 18:47.167
Well, good news. I'm fine.

18:47.251 --> 18:49.837
Great. Everything else okay?

18:49.920 --> 18:52.005
{\an3}Knee? Back? Neck?
Thyroid gland?

18:52.089 --> 18:54.174
What is this?
A fishing expedition?

18:54.258 --> 19:00.138
Actually, let me take myself
off the record here, Joe.

19:00.222 --> 19:03.350
Donna told me that you went
to see her father,

19:03.433 --> 19:05.644
{\an3}and you may have some
kind of heart condition.

19:08.814 --> 19:10.524
{\an1}She had no business
telling you that.

19:10.607 --> 19:13.026
{\an1}She only said anything
because she cares.

19:13.110 --> 19:15.737
{\an6}Come on, Brandon,
you know how
doctors work.

19:15.821 --> 19:17.406
{\an3}One tells you one thing,
one tells you another.

19:17.489 --> 19:19.116
I'm fine.

19:19.199 --> 19:20.242
You sure?

19:20.325 --> 19:24.121
Let me tell you something.

19:24.204 --> 19:26.248
When I was 16,
I had a really bad accident.

19:26.331 --> 19:27.791
I was rock climbing.

19:27.875 --> 19:30.919
Fell off a cliff
nearly 100 feet.

19:31.003 --> 19:32.212
Check out these scars.

19:34.506 --> 19:37.134
{\an3}Doctor said I'd
never walk again.

19:37.217 --> 19:39.094
But I did, and here I am,

19:39.177 --> 19:41.305
California University's
starting quarterback,

19:41.388 --> 19:44.766
and I'm taking the Condors
to the Rose Bowl next year.

19:44.850 --> 19:46.268
Every day of my life,

19:46.351 --> 19:49.021
I have dreamed
of playing in the pros.

19:49.104 --> 19:50.939
And if I had listened
to those doctors,

19:51.023 --> 19:52.733
I'd still be stuck
in that wheelchair.

19:54.192 --> 19:56.403
Yeah. I understand.

19:56.486 --> 19:59.406
I wish you could get Donna
to understand.

19:59.489 --> 20:01.575
I'll see what I can do.

20:04.578 --> 20:06.038
Oh, hey, Brandon.

20:06.121 --> 20:08.498
Is this going to be in
the newspaper tomorrow?

20:08.582 --> 20:12.127
No. Like I said,
this was off the record.

20:12.211 --> 20:14.129
Thanks, man.

20:14.212 --> 20:15.839
You got it.

20:38.236 --> 20:40.489
I hear there's stuff
coming through here.

20:40.572 --> 20:42.991
Can you help me out?

20:43.075 --> 20:44.910
What kind of stuff?

20:44.993 --> 20:46.411
Like a blizzard.

20:50.082 --> 20:52.084
Follow me.

21:02.094 --> 21:04.137
You a cop?

21:04.221 --> 21:05.430
{\an1}No, man.

21:05.514 --> 21:07.641
{\an3}That's funny.
I think I smell ham.

21:07.724 --> 21:09.810
You're smelling 60 bucks

21:09.893 --> 21:12.229
{\an3}if you get
me what I need.

21:12.312 --> 21:13.981
{\an1}You stay right here.
Don't move.

21:14.064 --> 21:17.150
I mean, don't move
until I come back.

21:17.234 --> 21:20.070
{\an3}I'm not
going anywhere.

21:33.083 --> 21:35.585
I got nothing.ge?

21:37.629 --> 21:39.423
(siren wailing in distance)

21:44.261 --> 21:45.929
I got what you wanted.

21:46.013 --> 21:48.265
{\an1}Oh, man,
took you long enough.

21:54.896 --> 21:55.772
Thanks.

21:55.856 --> 21:56.982
Watch your back.

21:57.065 --> 21:59.401
This is a lousy neighborhood.

22:12.539 --> 22:14.082
Did you get it?

22:14.166 --> 22:16.251
YGive me some..

22:16.334 --> 22:17.961
{\an3}No, let's wait till
we get home, all right?

22:18.045 --> 22:20.422
{\an3}This whole scene
gives me theCome on.

22:20.505 --> 22:21.798
Have some scotch.

22:21.882 --> 22:23.800
Just have a drink.h.

22:23.884 --> 22:26.053
{\an5}It'll make you
feel better, take
the edge oNo.

22:26.136 --> 22:27.763
{\an3}Driver, back to Venice,
Main Street.

22:27.846 --> 22:30.140
{\an5}(whispering):
Let's just get
out of here.

22:39.691 --> 22:41.902
What?
(clears throat)

22:41.985 --> 22:45.614
{\an1}Nothing. I'm just really
not in the mood, that's all.

22:45.697 --> 22:46.948
Okay.

22:47.032 --> 22:49.117
Is something wrong?

22:49.201 --> 22:52.788
{\an1}Would it fall
on deaf ears if it were?

22:52.871 --> 22:55.499
Uh, no.

22:55.582 --> 22:57.793
Could've fooled me.

22:57.876 --> 22:59.294
{\an3}(chuckles)

22:59.377 --> 23:01.588
All right, I'm lost.

23:03.548 --> 23:06.468
(sighs)
No, David, you're blind.

23:06.551 --> 23:09.012
{\an1}And I can't
figure out why.

23:09.096 --> 23:10.472
You've been down
this road before.

23:10.555 --> 23:12.974
You know the signs of drug use
better than anyone.

23:13.058 --> 23:14.935
Think about it.

23:15.018 --> 23:16.603
When was the last time
you saw Kelly

23:16.686 --> 23:18.605
before she waltzed in here
acting like Santa Claus?

23:21.358 --> 23:23.985
{\an1}And when was
the last timele.

23:24.069 --> 23:25.153
you saw Kelly come in here

23:25.237 --> 23:27.614
and shower <i> me</i> with gifts
of love and affection?

23:27.697 --> 23:29.991
Face it, David,

23:30.075 --> 23:31.660
she was high.

23:31.743 --> 23:34.579
So what should I do?

23:36.248 --> 23:37.999
I don't know.

23:38.083 --> 23:40.836
But you're her brother.

23:40.919 --> 23:43.088
You better do something.

23:53.765 --> 23:55.350
Something's wrong, Colin--
this stuff tastes weird.

23:55.433 --> 23:57.519
I'm not getting a buzz at all.

23:57.602 --> 23:59.020
{\an3}We got ripped
off, Kelly.

23:59.104 --> 24:00.897
I don't know
what this is,

24:00.981 --> 24:03.150
{\an3}but it sure the
hell isn't cocaine.

24:03.233 --> 24:04.985
Wh-What were you thinking?

24:05.068 --> 24:06.987
Didn't you taste it
before you got it?

24:07.070 --> 24:09.489
Yeah, sure, right in the middle
of a dark alley

24:09.573 --> 24:11.491
I'm gonna test the merchandise.

24:11.575 --> 24:12.993
{\an3}He could've had
a gun, Kelly.

24:13.076 --> 24:14.911
Congratulations,
you just blew 60 bucks.

24:14.995 --> 24:17.164
{\an1}Yeah, well,
if you hadn't hoovered up

24:17.247 --> 24:19.416
the last of the stash,
we'd be fine now, wouldn't we?

24:19.499 --> 24:21.001
Who are you calling?

24:21.084 --> 24:22.586
Paul.

24:22.669 --> 24:23.920
It's Colin.

24:24.004 --> 24:25.839
S.O.S., man.

24:25.922 --> 24:27.591
I thought you said
he didn't have any.

24:27.674 --> 24:30.510
Just give us
a pinch of yours until...

24:30.594 --> 24:32.512
I'll pay double.

24:32.596 --> 24:34.931
I said I'll pay double.

24:38.101 --> 24:39.019
Outstanding.

24:39.102 --> 24:40.395
I'll be right over.

24:42.647 --> 24:43.899
Bye.

24:43.982 --> 24:45.358
Go. Hurry up.

24:47.652 --> 24:48.695
(door opens, closes)

25:04.669 --> 25:06.421
{\an3}Get... get in
a good stretch,

25:06.504 --> 25:08.465
{\an3}because today we're up
for a serious run.

25:08.548 --> 25:09.090
Oh, of course we are.

25:09.174 --> 25:11.718
We're serious people here.

25:11.801 --> 25:14.221
{\an1}So, you know that
press release we got on Joe

25:14.304 --> 25:16.556
{\an1}from the athletic
Yeah.tment?

25:16.640 --> 25:18.308
Yeah, it's a snow job.

25:18.391 --> 25:20.727
{\an3}You mean there is something
wrong with his ankle?

25:20.810 --> 25:22.938
{\an1}No, not his ankle,
his heart.

25:23.021 --> 25:24.064
{\an3}His heart?

25:24.147 --> 25:26.441
{\an1}Yeah. I talked to Donna
off the record.

25:26.524 --> 25:30.403
She said Joe may have some sort
of congenital heart defect.

25:30.487 --> 25:31.279
Oh, no.

25:31.363 --> 25:33.990
{\an1}Oh, yes. But there are
differing opinions.

25:34.074 --> 25:35.450
{\an1}Two doctors,
two diagnoses.

25:35.533 --> 25:39.079
Turns out one of the doctors
is Donna's father.

25:39.162 --> 25:40.747
And doc number two?

25:40.830 --> 25:42.791
Recommended
by the athletic department.

25:43.833 --> 25:45.460
Oh, man.

25:45.543 --> 25:46.920
{\an3}So, what's Joe
going to do?

25:47.003 --> 25:48.964
{\an1}He's listening to the guy
that says he's fine

25:49.047 --> 25:50.590
{\an1}so he can keep
playing football.

25:50.674 --> 25:52.592
{\an3}How convenient for
the athletic department.

25:52.676 --> 25:54.970
{\an3}So, when are you
gonna interview Joe?

25:55.053 --> 25:56.137
I'm not.

25:56.221 --> 25:58.056
We aren't covering this story.

25:58.139 --> 25:59.140
Are you crazy?

25:59.224 --> 26:00.976
The athletic department
is putting up a smoke screen

26:01.059 --> 26:02.978
around its star quarterback,
and you're gonna do nothing?

26:03.061 --> 26:04.938
{\an1}I told you, it was
off the record.

26:05.021 --> 26:06.064
Well, then go
<i>on</i> the record.

26:06.147 --> 26:08.024
Look.

26:08.108 --> 26:09.234
Joe's my friend.

26:09.317 --> 26:12.696
If we even hint that there
may be something wrong with him,

26:12.779 --> 26:14.239
we could jeopardize
his entire career.

26:14.322 --> 26:16.908
No, Brandon.

26:16.992 --> 26:19.327
{\an3}Joe is doing that
all by himself.

26:27.502 --> 26:28.628
{\an3}This sucks.

26:28.712 --> 26:30.547
{\an1}Yeah, it's penance
for our sins--

26:30.630 --> 26:32.132
it's supposed to suck.

26:32.215 --> 26:34.009
Welcome jawbreakers.

26:34.092 --> 26:35.385
Of course,
I mean lawbreakers.

26:35.468 --> 26:36.553
In case you're lost,

26:36.636 --> 26:38.388
this is the Last Laugh
Traffic School.

26:38.471 --> 26:39.848
My name is Lou Nebitts,

26:39.931 --> 26:42.017
but before you go
calling me "Mrs. Nebbish,"

26:42.100 --> 26:44.185
let me remind you
that I have control

26:44.269 --> 26:45.353
over your driving records.

26:45.437 --> 26:48.189
So feel free to laugh
whenever I say something funny.

26:48.273 --> 26:49.024
(laughs)

26:49.107 --> 26:50.191
That wasn't funny.

26:50.275 --> 26:51.359
You're telling me.

26:51.443 --> 26:52.694
Any comedian
with talent

26:52.777 --> 26:54.821
{\an6}is not gonna
be headlining
traffic school.

26:54.904 --> 26:56.031
NEBITTS:
All right, then,

26:56.114 --> 27:00.076
who can tell me what is the
cause of most moving violations?

27:00.160 --> 27:01.328
Speeding?

27:01.411 --> 27:03.079
{\an1}NEBITTS:
Illegal turns?

27:03.163 --> 27:06.041
Internal combustion.

27:06.124 --> 27:08.710
Have you ever taken
this class before?

27:08.793 --> 27:09.711
No.

27:09.794 --> 27:10.712
Obviously not.

27:10.795 --> 27:12.047
Because you don't know

27:12.130 --> 27:13.715
the first rule
of Lou Nebitts' traffic school--

27:13.798 --> 27:16.217
"Never be funnier
than the teacher."

27:16.301 --> 27:17.886
(sarcastic laugh)

27:17.969 --> 27:19.054
But seriously, folks,

27:19.137 --> 27:21.139
the major cause
of most moving violations

27:21.222 --> 27:23.391
is poor time management.

27:23.475 --> 27:26.227
So, what'd they
nab you for, Shecky?

27:26.311 --> 27:27.228
Oh, this is all her fault.

27:27.312 --> 27:29.022
{\an3}CLARE:
Yeah, you wish.

27:29.105 --> 27:30.398
You know, I should've trusted
my instincts and gone

27:30.482 --> 27:32.275
{\an1}Then why
don't you justffic school.

27:32.359 --> 27:33.693
change your major to home ec?

27:33.777 --> 27:34.903
NEBITTS:
This seems like there's

27:34.986 --> 27:37.572
a little unresolved anger--
maybe you two should have gone

27:37.655 --> 27:39.407
to conflict-avoidance
traffic school.

27:39.491 --> 27:42.035
Then we never
would ha(coughs)ou, Lou.

27:42.118 --> 27:44.245
I don't... know him,
he's just...

27:44.329 --> 27:46.081
Aren't they cute?
The fighting Wallendas.

27:46.164 --> 27:48.041
Tell me, do you fight in bed?

27:48.124 --> 27:49.459
Yep.

27:49.542 --> 27:51.211
{\an1}It's none
of your business.

27:51.294 --> 27:52.087
(laughter)

27:52.170 --> 27:54.047
{\an1}And what are you
laughing at?

27:54.130 --> 27:55.965
(laughs)

27:57.884 --> 28:00.053
