{\an1}Kelly dropped
that off for you.

28:02.180 --> 28:03.598
I don't know.

28:03.681 --> 28:05.266
{\an1}I'm waiting
to find out-- open it.

28:05.350 --> 28:07.102
No occasion.ccasion?

28:07.185 --> 28:08.478
She and Colin came by

28:08.561 --> 28:11.314
{\an1}giving gifts to all
her friends-- me included.

28:14.317 --> 28:16.236
It's a Mont Blanc pen.

28:16.319 --> 28:17.987
{\an1}A sterling silver
Mont Blanc pen.

28:18.071 --> 28:19.781
{\an1}Do you know
what that's worth?

28:19.864 --> 28:21.241
That's, like, over $600.

28:21.324 --> 28:22.492
No way.

28:22.575 --> 28:24.119
They must've been flying.

28:24.202 --> 28:25.954
Either that or Kelly's
gone completely crazy.

28:26.037 --> 28:28.957
{\an3}Wait a second, are you
saying that Kelly was high?

28:29.040 --> 28:30.750
I don't think it, I know it.

28:30.834 --> 28:33.253
I can't believe that.

28:33.336 --> 28:35.422
You know what,
you're like everybody else.

28:35.505 --> 28:37.590
You can't believe
that little Miss Perfect

28:37.674 --> 28:38.842
can do anything wrong.

29:00.113 --> 29:01.531
(muffled groan)

29:01.614 --> 29:04.200
The light is driving me crazy--
I can't get to sleep.

29:04.284 --> 29:05.493
It's not the light

29:05.577 --> 29:07.495
that's keeping you up,
believe me.

29:08.705 --> 29:12.000
I feel like
I haven't slept in days.

29:12.083 --> 29:14.002
You haven't.

29:14.085 --> 29:16.504
I can't keep doing this.

29:16.588 --> 29:19.048
(phone rings)

29:19.132 --> 29:20.925
Aren't you gonna get that?

29:21.009 --> 29:23.219
No. I don't want
to talk to anybody.

29:23.303 --> 29:24.929
COLIN (recorded):
All right, you called.

29:25.013 --> 29:26.139
What's up?

29:26.222 --> 29:27.056
BRANDON:
Hey, Colin.

29:27.140 --> 29:28.141
Uh, it's me, Brandon.

29:28.224 --> 29:30.018
Actually, I'm calling for Kelly.

29:30.101 --> 29:32.520
Well, I guess I-I'm calling
for both of you guys.

29:32.604 --> 29:34.856
Thanks for the awesome pen,
although I have no idea

29:34.939 --> 29:35.857
what I did to deserve it.

29:35.940 --> 29:38.359
Just wanted to make sure
you guys are all right.

29:38.443 --> 29:40.195
People are starting to wonder.

29:40.278 --> 29:42.113
Give me a call, Kel. Bye.

29:42.197 --> 29:44.073
(line hangs up,
answering machine beeps)

29:44.157 --> 29:45.366
<i>Are</i> we all right?

29:45.450 --> 29:47.368
Wish I could
say the same.

29:47.452 --> 29:50.205
I got to get out of here--
I need some sleep.

29:50.288 --> 29:52.207
You'll be fine
once you crash.

29:52.290 --> 29:54.459
(sighs)ake some downers.

29:58.129 --> 30:00.173
Makes for softer landing.

30:03.426 --> 30:06.554
Lay down, and try
to close your eyes, okay?

30:06.638 --> 30:08.223
No, I can't.

30:08.306 --> 30:09.557
I want my own bed.

30:09.641 --> 30:11.142
I'm gonna go home, okay?

30:17.106 --> 30:20.276
(door opens, closes)

30:23.029 --> 30:25.323
MAN (over video):
There's a war going on

30:25.406 --> 30:27.075
on the highways of our country,

30:27.158 --> 30:28.243
and innocents
are being slaughtered

30:28.326 --> 30:31.454
by the drunken, the drugged,

30:31.538 --> 30:34.791
and those who just don't think.

30:34.874 --> 30:36.751
What right do they have

30:36.834 --> 30:39.587
to endanger my life, to threaten
my wife and my children?

30:39.671 --> 30:40.922
I mean, what right...

30:41.005 --> 30:42.757
Great flick you took me to.

30:42.840 --> 30:44.259
Enough already.

30:44.342 --> 30:47.095
I'm sick of being blamed
for something that you started.

30:47.178 --> 30:49.097
{\an3}Shh!

30:49.180 --> 30:52.058
You're a big boy--
you could've just said no.

30:52.141 --> 30:53.935
That's easy for you to say.

30:56.646 --> 30:58.314
We hope you enjoyed

30:58.398 --> 31:00.984
our feature presentation
of <i> Red Asphalt III.</i>

31:01.067 --> 31:04.487
Siskel and Ebert gave
this classic "two thumbs off."

31:07.490 --> 31:09.784
Good. You're finally
getting the picture.

31:09.867 --> 31:11.244
Speeding is no laughing matter.

31:11.327 --> 31:13.913
Now, why don't we take
that bathroom break.

31:13.997 --> 31:17.000
Some of you look
like you could use it.

31:20.253 --> 31:23.089
Yeah, it's Max.
How's it going?

31:23.172 --> 31:24.424
What?

31:24.507 --> 31:25.883
They didn't show up?

31:25.967 --> 31:28.094
But we tape in two hours!

31:33.224 --> 31:35.768
Um, yeah, look, um, don't worry,

31:35.852 --> 31:38.813
I'll figure something out, okay?

31:38.896 --> 31:41.316
{\an3}(chuckles)
Crisis on the set.

31:41.399 --> 31:43.484
Hey, listen, uh,
my name's Max Roman.

31:43.568 --> 31:46.863
I'm here because
I pulled a 180 on PCH,

31:46.946 --> 31:48.823
but I also happen to be
a producer of <i> Back Talk.</i>

31:48.906 --> 31:51.034
{\an1}Yeah, channel
nine, right?r watch it?

31:51.117 --> 31:53.161
WrongRight, right.

31:53.244 --> 31:54.996
(chuckling)

31:55.079 --> 31:57.874
You know, you two...
you two are dynamite.

31:57.957 --> 31:59.208
{\an3}No, no, look,
I want you

31:59.292 --> 32:01.669
{\an1}to come with me when
we get sprung out of here,

32:01.753 --> 32:03.338
and I want you
to tape a segment.

32:03.421 --> 32:04.714
It's called
"Tangled Up in Love."

32:04.797 --> 32:05.882
It's about couples
who keep fighting

32:05.965 --> 32:07.383
{\an1}all the time,
and we'll do that whole

32:07.467 --> 32:09.052
love-hate thing, huh?

32:09.135 --> 32:10.511
{\an1}Well, there's
no love-hate here.

32:10.595 --> 32:11.846
{\an3}Speak for
yourself, honOw!

32:11.929 --> 32:12.847
Now, it's not great money,

32:12.930 --> 32:15.058
but it is only gonna take
a couple of hours.

32:15.141 --> 32:16.059
{\an1}So, what do
you say, huh?

32:16.142 --> 32:16.726
Come on-- from one

32:16.809 --> 32:18.269
high-risk driver to another?

32:18.353 --> 32:20.021
Forget it.

32:20.104 --> 32:21.397
(Max chuckles)

32:21.481 --> 32:24.067
You're gonna be perfect.

32:24.150 --> 32:25.985
SUSAN:
<i>Listen, um,</i>

32:26.069 --> 32:27.862
{\an1}I heard from
the athletic department

32:27.945 --> 32:30.073
about Joe's heart.

32:30.156 --> 32:31.699
You did?

32:31.783 --> 32:33.868
{\an3}Yeah. Um...

32:33.951 --> 32:36.037
{\an3}I really feel bad
for him, Donna,

32:36.120 --> 32:37.705
and you, too.

32:37.789 --> 32:39.999
Yeah, well, the worst part is,

32:40.083 --> 32:42.085
Joe's pushing himself
even harder now.

32:42.168 --> 32:44.837
You know your father
is a great doctor.

32:44.921 --> 32:46.881
Um, what exactly

32:46.964 --> 32:47.840
was his diagnosis anyway?

32:47.924 --> 32:50.385
{\an3}I mean, I know it was
some type of, um,

32:50.468 --> 32:51.552
congenital heart defect.

32:51.636 --> 32:54.055
Well, I-I thought you talked

32:54.138 --> 32:56.349
to the athletic department--
they didn't tell you?

32:59.310 --> 33:01.354
{\an3}Um, you know,
actually, I got to go.

33:01.437 --> 33:03.731
{\an3}Um, maybe we can have
coffee some other time.

33:03.815 --> 33:05.191
Wait, Susan.

33:05.274 --> 33:08.111
You're not gonna write a story
about this, are you?

33:10.154 --> 33:11.906
I don't know.

33:14.534 --> 33:16.160
Hey, Susan.

33:18.079 --> 33:19.497
Hey.

33:22.333 --> 33:23.960
{\an1}What were you talking
to Susan about?

33:24.043 --> 33:26.587
Uh, nothing.

33:26.671 --> 33:29.215
Just like you were talking
to Brandon about nothing?

33:29.298 --> 33:31.008
These people run

33:31.092 --> 33:32.760
the school newspaper, Donna.

33:32.844 --> 33:35.096
These people are
my friends, Joe.

33:35.179 --> 33:37.098
{\an1}Oh, yeah, until they
think they've got a story.

33:37.181 --> 33:38.224
Then they're nobody's friends.

33:38.307 --> 33:40.101
That is not true.

33:40.184 --> 33:42.437
You know what?

33:42.520 --> 33:44.772
{\an3}I kind of hope they do
write a story about you.

33:44.856 --> 33:48.067
Because then maybe you'll pay
attention to common sense.

33:48.151 --> 33:50.069
If <i> The Condor</i> even suggests

33:50.153 --> 33:52.405
that there's something wrong
with me, I'm damaged goods.

33:52.488 --> 33:54.949
{\an1}That ends all hopes
I have for a pro career.

33:57.160 --> 33:59.412
What kind of career are you
gonna have if you're dead?

33:59.495 --> 34:01.038
Whose side are you on?

34:01.122 --> 34:02.790
Yours--

34:02.874 --> 34:05.168
if you'd just open your eyes
wide enough to see it.

34:25.521 --> 34:26.438
David.

34:26.522 --> 34:27.440
Hey.

34:27.523 --> 34:29.817
What's going on?

34:29.900 --> 34:32.152
{\an1}Nothing. I'm just looking
for Kelly. Is she here?

34:32.235 --> 34:33.862
{\an3}No, man, she got bored
watching me work.

34:33.946 --> 34:35.406
She took off a while ago.

34:35.489 --> 34:37.158
Is something wrong?

34:38.409 --> 34:40.369
{\an1}I don't know. I haven't
seen her in a while.

34:40.453 --> 34:41.829
{\an3}She's been
hanging out here.

34:41.913 --> 34:43.623
{\an3}Actually, she hasn't
been feeling that great.

34:43.706 --> 34:45.500
I've been taking good
care of her, though.

34:45.583 --> 34:47.376
That's good.

34:47.460 --> 34:49.170
Because I really care
about her, you know?

34:49.253 --> 34:52.005
Yeah, so do I.

34:52.089 --> 34:54.132
I'd do anything for Kelly,
you know that.

34:55.927 --> 34:57.428
Even share your drugs with her?

35:00.932 --> 35:03.017
Is that the line Valerie's
been feeding you?

35:03.100 --> 35:06.020
She's expressed her concern.

35:06.103 --> 35:08.022
I bet she has,
and I bet you

35:08.105 --> 35:09.982
{\an3}jumped all over it,
too, didn't you?

35:10.066 --> 35:11.692
{\an3}You and your girlfriend
are way off-base.

35:11.776 --> 35:13.361
Just stop, all right?

35:13.444 --> 35:14.821
I know when someone's using.

35:14.904 --> 35:16.030
I can tell by looking.

35:16.114 --> 35:16.989
Kelly's clean.

35:17.073 --> 35:18.199
So am I.

35:18.282 --> 35:19.367
Don't make me laugh.

35:19.450 --> 35:20.868
You know what?

35:20.952 --> 35:23.037
I don't need you
or any other 12-step convert

35:23.120 --> 35:25.331
coming into my house,
telling me my business.

35:27.291 --> 35:29.085
I don't care what you do,

35:29.168 --> 35:31.504
but if you don't stop giving
your drugs to my sister,

35:31.587 --> 35:34.173
the only thing you're gonna
find up your nose is my fist.

35:37.093 --> 35:38.094
You finished?

36:03.828 --> 36:04.453
Yeah, Beverly Hills, please.

36:04.537 --> 36:07.164
The number for a
Dr. John Martin.

36:08.165 --> 36:10.585
{\an1}What do you
think you're doing?

36:10.668 --> 36:12.086
I'm just checking the facts.

36:12.170 --> 36:13.421
Don't look at
me like that.

36:13.504 --> 36:15.256
{\an1}You're building a story,
one that I told you

36:15.339 --> 36:16.924
was officially off the record.

36:17.008 --> 36:17.925
For you, maybe.

36:18.009 --> 36:19.010
Look, I talked to Donna.

36:19.093 --> 36:21.095
{\an3}I talked to Kip Hardwick
in the Athletic Department.

36:21.178 --> 36:22.096
I talked to Dr. Levin,

36:22.179 --> 36:24.432
{\an3}the one who gave Joe
that clean bill of health.

36:24.515 --> 36:25.766
I've done it all on my own

36:25.850 --> 36:27.435
without involving
or compromising you.

36:27.518 --> 36:28.936
You're unbelievable.

36:29.020 --> 36:30.938
Look, I don't even
have to use Joe's name.

36:31.022 --> 36:32.773
I can slant the whole story

36:32.857 --> 36:35.234
{\an3}around the manipulation of
the Athletic Department.

36:35.318 --> 36:38.195
The religion of football,
winning at any cost.

36:38.279 --> 36:39.614
And what about getting
a story at any cost?

36:39.697 --> 36:41.324
You're as bad as they are.

36:41.407 --> 36:42.199
Joe is putting himself at risk

36:42.283 --> 36:43.201
by ignoring the advice
of Dr. Martin,

36:43.284 --> 36:45.745
a widely respected
cardiologist, I might add.

36:45.828 --> 36:47.622
That's Joe's decision
to make, not yours.

36:47.705 --> 36:48.581
Look, I know

36:48.664 --> 36:50.249
Joe is your friend,
Brandon, but how much

36:50.333 --> 36:51.709
are you willing
to risk for friendship?

36:51.792 --> 36:53.628
You mean to tell me
if you found out Joe was

36:53.711 --> 36:55.922
{\an3}point-shaving you wouldn't
run a story on that?

36:56.005 --> 36:58.132
Now, you're comparing
horseshoes and hand grenades.

36:58.215 --> 36:59.884
Am I?

37:01.552 --> 37:02.970
Drop the story.

37:16.817 --> 37:18.444
There you are.

37:18.527 --> 37:19.904
Hey. What's up?

37:19.987 --> 37:21.447
What the hell you
trying to pull?

37:21.530 --> 37:22.865
Excuse me?

37:22.949 --> 37:24.158
{\an1}Siccing your
boyfriend on me?

37:24.241 --> 37:25.493
Real smooth, Val--
what other tricks

37:25.576 --> 37:26.786
can you make
him do for you?

37:26.869 --> 37:28.704
Wait, I don't know
what you're talking about.

37:28.788 --> 37:29.664
{\an1}Like hell
you don't.

37:29.747 --> 37:31.624
You sent David
over to threaten <i> me?</i>

37:31.707 --> 37:33.292
{\an3}Hey, I didn't send
David anywhere.

37:33.376 --> 37:34.835
He figured out what was going on

37:34.919 --> 37:37.129
with you and Kelly all
by himself. We all did.

37:37.213 --> 37:38.714
Yeah, well, you're
all out of line.

37:38.798 --> 37:41.634
{\an1}You and everyone else, leave
Kelly and me alone, all right?

37:41.717 --> 37:43.302
Stay out of our lives!

37:43.386 --> 37:45.054
Colin. Listen to me.

37:45.137 --> 37:48.057
They wouldn't be in your
life without Kelly, okay?

37:48.140 --> 37:49.934
They care about
her, not you.

37:51.894 --> 37:53.813
I'm the only one who does.

37:57.108 --> 37:59.026
Just keep them off my back.

38:13.499 --> 38:15.251
{\an3}What the hell are
we doing here?

38:15.334 --> 38:17.586
Why don't you
tell me, Clare?

38:17.670 --> 38:20.423
{\an3}I don't see the
point, all right?

38:20.506 --> 38:21.465
This is the point.

38:21.549 --> 38:24.719
I argue. You bitch. We fight.

38:24.802 --> 38:26.887
Now we get to do it
on national television.

38:26.971 --> 38:28.806
This is a local show, Steve.

38:28.889 --> 38:30.891
This is local?

38:30.975 --> 38:31.851
{\an1}We don't
get national

38:31.934 --> 38:32.768
{\an1}coverage
No. this?

38:32.852 --> 38:33.853
What are we doing here?

38:33.936 --> 38:35.521
{\an3}ROMAN:
My Hey, hey, hey.

38:35.604 --> 38:36.731
{\an3}Time out, okay?
Now, don't start in

38:36.814 --> 38:38.733
{\an3}on each other until
we're rolling.

38:38.816 --> 38:40.735
You guys are gonna be great.

38:40.818 --> 38:42.069
DIRECTOR:
And here we go!

38:42.153 --> 38:45.072
In five, four, three...

38:45.156 --> 38:46.240
two...and...

38:46.323 --> 38:48.284
(applause, whistles)

38:50.036 --> 38:52.747
Hi. Today on <i> Back Talk,</i>

38:52.830 --> 38:53.748
"Couples Who Can't Stop
Fighting."

38:53.831 --> 38:54.957
Ladies and gentlemen,

38:55.041 --> 38:57.251
let's welcome our first
combative couple,

38:57.335 --> 38:58.419
Steve and Clare.

38:58.502 --> 39:00.212
(applause, cheers)

39:03.507 --> 39:05.760
So, Steve, who's guilty
of all the bickering?

39:05.843 --> 39:06.761
Let me explain.

39:06.844 --> 39:07.678
{\an3}No, I'm not
gonna let you.

39:07.762 --> 39:09.430
{\an6}No, not if it
involves any
more blame.

39:09.513 --> 39:10.765
{\an1}Blame? it.

39:10.848 --> 39:11.682
What's he blame you for, Clare?

39:11.766 --> 39:14.602
{\an3}What does he bl...?
Okay, well, um...

39:14.685 --> 39:16.812
street racing,
getting busted,

39:16.896 --> 39:17.605
winding up in traffic school...

39:17.688 --> 39:18.731
Okay, okay!

39:18.814 --> 39:20.066
I'm not blaming you anymore.

39:20.149 --> 39:21.108
Thank you, okay?

39:21.192 --> 39:22.234
I want to thank you.

39:22.318 --> 39:23.235
{\an1}CLARE:
What?

39:23.319 --> 39:24.445
I'm a little lost here, Steve.

39:24.528 --> 39:25.446
{\an3}Me, too.

39:25.529 --> 39:26.280
Well, don't you see?

39:26.364 --> 39:27.782
{\an1}Don't you see where
all this fighting

39:27.865 --> 39:29.241
{\an1}and bickering
and arguing

39:29.325 --> 39:30.618
has gotten us?

39:30.701 --> 39:31.660
On some dinky local talk show?

39:31.744 --> 39:32.620
{\an1}No.

39:32.703 --> 39:34.580
Behind the wheels
of two speeding cars.

39:34.663 --> 39:35.623
I'm glad we
got caught.

39:35.706 --> 39:37.166
Thank God we
got caught,

39:37.249 --> 39:40.002
because I could've
gotten you hurt... or worse.

39:41.712 --> 39:43.631
Well, it's not all your fault.

39:43.714 --> 39:44.965
If anything ever
happened to you

39:45.049 --> 39:46.675
or that cute little
brain of yours,

39:46.759 --> 39:48.552
I don't think I could
ever forgive myself.

39:50.054 --> 39:53.015
AUDIENCE:
Aw...

39:54.683 --> 39:55.601
(applause)

39:55.684 --> 39:56.602
(groans)

39:56.685 --> 39:58.020
What do you mean,

39:58.104 --> 40:02.817
my cute <i> little</i> brain?

40:02.900 --> 40:04.318
It was an endearment term.

40:04.402 --> 40:06.779
{\an4}CLARE:
Oh, it didn't sound
very endearing to me.

40:06.862 --> 40:08.614
You know, you calling me cute,
that's kind of what got us

40:08.697 --> 40:10.533
in this whole mess in the
first place. You remember?

40:10.616 --> 40:11.951
{\an1}Would you prefer "sporty"?
You got a cute,

40:12.034 --> 40:13.119
You're impossible.n?

40:13.202 --> 40:14.787
Yeah, you're impos...

40:14.870 --> 40:15.704
{\an1}The only
point'soint at me!

40:15.788 --> 40:17.456
{\an1}on top of your head,
but you tease your hair,

40:17.540 --> 40:18.874
Don't point at me!.

40:18.958 --> 40:20.876
{\an1}I won't point at you, okay?
I won't even talk to you?

40:22.878 --> 40:24.380
(door closes)

40:25.965 --> 40:26.882
Kel.

40:26.966 --> 40:28.467
God, am I glad to see you.

40:28.551 --> 40:29.635
Hey.

40:29.718 --> 40:30.678
You don't look so good.

40:30.761 --> 40:31.679
Are you okay?

40:31.762 --> 40:32.680
Oh, yeah, yeah.

40:32.763 --> 40:34.098
I'm just tired.

40:34.181 --> 40:35.641
Oh, yeah. I'm beat, too.

40:35.724 --> 40:37.560
Joe and I have been on such
an emotional roller-coaster

40:37.643 --> 40:38.811
the past few days,
you wouldn't even

40:38.894 --> 40:40.521
believe it, Kel..

40:40.604 --> 40:41.522
Kel?

40:41.605 --> 40:43.190
Hmm?

40:44.650 --> 40:45.693
Nothing.

40:45.776 --> 40:47.069
I just, I thought we could talk.

40:47.153 --> 40:48.612
Can't it wait?

40:48.696 --> 40:50.698
I came home to get some sleep.

40:50.781 --> 40:53.409
Oh. Yeah, I just,

40:53.492 --> 40:55.035
I haven't see you in so long,

40:55.119 --> 40:56.704
and I kind of needed
your advice.

40:56.787 --> 40:58.622
I can't do it right now.

40:58.706 --> 41:00.583
I'm too tired.

41:09.800 --> 41:12.344
(indistinct shouting)

41:40.498 --> 41:42.500
He looks healthy enough.

41:42.583 --> 41:44.001
What are you doing here?

41:46.337 --> 41:48.088
{\an1}I, uh... just thought
I'd come by

41:48.172 --> 41:50.174
and tell you that
I wrote the story.

41:52.509 --> 41:54.094
(sighs)

41:54.178 --> 41:57.097
"Medical Condition
of Condor Q.B. Questionable.

41:57.181 --> 42:00.434
Possible Athletic
Department Cover-Up."

42:00.518 --> 42:03.562
{\an3}I can't believe you're
gonna run this.

42:05.147 --> 42:06.565
I'm not.

42:12.363 --> 42:14.448
That was some
of the best stuff I ever wrote.

42:14.531 --> 42:16.867
Then why'd you tear it up?

42:19.703 --> 42:22.623
{\an1}I guess I started
thinking about my sister.

42:22.706 --> 42:24.124
And what she meant to me.

42:24.208 --> 42:25.751
And...?

42:25.834 --> 42:28.420
And... I don't

42:28.504 --> 42:29.880
want to hurt Joe.

42:33.175 --> 42:35.177
There's always another story.

42:35.261 --> 42:37.930
Well, I appreciate that.

42:38.013 --> 42:39.807
I'm sure Joe will, too.

42:44.687 --> 42:47.314
What if he wasn't a friend?
Would you run the story then?

42:48.774 --> 42:49.858
Yeah, I would.

43:02.705 --> 43:04.832
{\an1}I hope we're doing
the right thing, Brandon.

43:04.915 --> 43:07.626
{\an1}What if there's
something wrong with him?

43:07.710 --> 43:09.003
